Reasoning: The paper focuses on studying viral images from a computer vision perspective, using state-of-the-art image features to predict virality of individual images and relative virality in pairs of images. This suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze the images, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions using metadata from Reddit to define a virality score, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses how human prediction of image virality varies with different contexts, which could fall under the social and information networks (cs.SD) sub-category.
